properties.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued January 22 at 3:18PM PST until January 23 at 8:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Minor coastal flooding expected.

* WHERE...Admiralty Inlet Area.

* WHEN...From 2 AM to 8 AM PST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Flooding of lots, parks, and roads with only
isolated road closures expected.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The combination of high astronomical tide,
strong winds, and low pressure will result in minor tidal
overflow at Port Townsend. High tide at Port Townsend is around
500 AM PST at 9.35 feet. The tidal anomaly is 0.5 to 1 foot.
properties.instruction:
If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be
closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of
unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone
property.

NWSheadline: COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 2 AM TO 8 AM PST THURSDAY
